                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/971: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="42" xml:id="d811fn42">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, to the Chargé in Guatemala as telegram No. 69, referring
                        to Legation’s telegram No. 133, October 28, 7 p.m.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-12T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 12, 1929—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>82. Legation’s 107, November 7, 4 p.m. The Department desires to fix a date for
                    the convening of the boundary conference which will be most convenient to the
                    Governments of Honduras and Guatemala. Please ascertain and report by telegraph
                    the approximate time when Honduras will be prepared to be represented at the
                    conference. A similar telegram is being addressed to the Legation at
                    Guatemala.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
